headline: Interactive Brokers January Surge Tests Valuation And Growth Expectations
summary: Interactive Brokers Group reported January 2026 figures showing higher trading activity across its platform. The company also reported growth in client accounts and total client equity for the month. These operational metrics point to stronger engagement from both new and existing clients in early 2026. For investors watching NasdaqGS:IBKR, these fresh January numbers add important context to a share price of $75.27. The stock is up 12.0% over the past month and 35.4% over the past year,...

headline: Interactive Brokers reports January DARTs 27% higher than prior year

headline: Interactive Brokers Group to Present at BofA Securities 2026 Financial Services Conference
